	abstract = {Breast cancer remains a major health challenge, and improving detection methods is crucial for better outcomes. This study aims to enhance breast cancer detection by comparing two advanced algorithms. Using a trained dataset, we evaluate how well each algorithm predicts breast cancer risk. Both algorithms were tested with 10 samples each. The SVM algorithm, a supervised learning technique grounded in statistical learning theory, showed impressive accuracy in detecting breast cancer, achieving 95.70\%. On the other hand, the CNN algorithm, known for its powerful classification and prediction capabilities, achieved an accuracy of 90.81\%. For both algorithms, we set the significance level to(p {\textless} 0.05) to ensure robust results. Our findings suggest that the SVM algorithm outperforms the CNN algorithm in breast cancer prediction.},
